<p><a name="Sampling_in_other_contexts" id="Sampling_in_other_contexts"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Sampling_(music)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=17" title="Edit section: Sampling in other contexts">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Sampling in other contexts</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="/wiki/Appropriation_(art)" title="Appropriation (art)">Appropriation (art)</a> - (Visual arts) often refers to the use of borrowed elements in the creation of new work.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Collage" title="Collage">Collage</a> - a work of visual arts made from an assemblage of different forms, thus creating a new whole.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Cut-up_technique" title="Cut-up technique">Cut-up technique</a> - an aleatory literary technique or genre in which a <a href="/wiki/Writing" title="Writing">writing</a> is cut up at <a href="/wiki/Random" title="Random" class="mw-redirect">random</a> and rearranged to create a new text.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Found_footage" title="Found footage">Found footage</a> - a method of compiling films partly or entirely of footage which has not been created by the filmmaker.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Papier_coll%C3%A9" title="Papier collé">Papier collé</a> - a painting technique and type of collage.</li>
</ul>
