<p><a name="External_links" id="External_links"></a></p>
<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Sampling_(music)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=20" title="Edit section: External links">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">External links</span></h2>
<p><a href="http://www.samplesdb.com" class="external text" title="http://www.samplesdb.com" rel="nofollow">SamplesDB</a> - user-generated database of samples with about 15,000 samples in its database.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.hipsamples.com" class="external text" title="http://www.hipsamples.com" rel="nofollow">HipSamples</a> is creating a database full of samples and tutorials related to sampling in various software applications.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.samplespot.com" class="external text" title="http://www.samplespot.com" rel="nofollow">SampleSpot</a> - biggest online database of samples, cover art and download links.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.the-breaks.com" class="external text" title="http://www.the-breaks.com" rel="nofollow">the-breaks</a> AKA The (Rap) Sample FAQ, samples and their sources in all forms of music.</p>
<p><a href="http://www.whosampled.com" class="external text" title="http://www.whosampled.com" rel="nofollow">WhoSampled</a> - a database of sampled music.</p>


